  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesised that cyclosporine A administration at the onset of
      cardiopulmonary resuscitation, by inhibiting the mitochondrial permeability transition pore,
      could prevent the post cardiac arrest syndrome and improve outcomes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
